  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThere are `error` logs emitted when messages are received but their queues are full. As an example:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/0177b9286edfdeb2782f74fc7fb1392b6459bfaa/beacon_node/network/src/beacon_processor/work_reprocessing_queue.rs#L340-L345\r\n\r\nThese errors can be triggered once per attestation, so it will emit thousands logs at a time if the attestation delay queue is full:\r\n\r\n```\r\nERRO Attestation delay queue is full         msg: check system clock, queue_size: 16384\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to Resolve\r\n\r\nOver in another part of the `BeaconProcessor`, I've implemented the `TimeLatch`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/0177b9286edfdeb2782f74fc7fb1392b6459bfaa/beacon_node/network/src/beacon_processor/mod.rs#L745-L762\r\n\r\nThe `Timelatch` is used to limit the rate of \"queue full\" messages:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/0177b9286edfdeb2782f74fc7fb1392b6459bfaa/beacon_node/network/src/beacon_processor/mod.rs#L1285-L1292\r\n\r\nI recommend we do the same thing in the `work_reprocessing_queue`",
